INSERT INTO bytes.bytes (id, author_id, title, body, code_snippet, language, embedding, type, is_active, created_at, updated_at) VALUES (
  '9ce175aa-4350-4931-a5f5-35892fc4e90f',
  '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',
  $escape$Qwik Prop Typing — Discriminated Unions for Variants, Zero `any`$escape$,
  $escape$Qwik's `component$` accepts a generic type parameter — use it. When a component has visual variants (Button, Badge, Alert), reach for discriminated unions instead of a pile of optional props typed as `string | undefined`.

Each union member narrows the shape: an `'icon'` variant requires `icon: string`, while a `'static'` variant omits `onClick$` entirely. TypeScript's control-flow narrowing then works inside the render logic — after checking `props.variant === 'icon'`, `props.icon` is fully typed with no assertions needed.

Avoid `any` entirely. If a prop varies by variant, it belongs in the union, not as `prop?: any`. Qwik serializes props across the server/client boundary, so loose types hide serialization mismatches until runtime.

One critical Qwik caveat: event handler props use the `$` suffix convention and must be typed as `QRL<() => void>`, not the plain function type `() => void`. The TypeScript compiler won't flag the difference, but Qwik's optimizer will silently fail to lazy-load the handler on hydration. Import `QRL` from `@builder.io/qwik` and type every serialized callback explicitly.$escape$,
  $escape$import { component$, type QRL } from '@builder.io/qwik';

type Base = { label: string };
type PrimaryProps = Base & { variant: 'primary'; onClick$: QRL<() => void> };
type IconProps   = Base & { variant: 'icon';    icon: string; onClick$: QRL<() => void> };
type StaticProps = Base & { variant: 'static' };

type ButtonProps = PrimaryProps | IconProps | StaticProps;

export const Button = component$<ButtonProps>((props) => {
  if (props.variant === 'static') return <span>{props.label}</span>;
  if (props.variant === 'icon')   return <button onClick$={props.onClick$}>{props.icon}</button>;
  return <button onClick$={props.onClick$}>{props.label}</button>;
});$escape$,
  $escape$typescript$escape$,
