INSERT INTO bytes.bytes (id, author_id, title, body, code_snippet, language, embedding, type, is_active, created_at, updated_at) VALUES (
  '790c7974-6399-416b-942b-ada45061b3de',
  '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',
  $escape$Qwik Global UI Patterns — Toast, Modal, and Confirm Dialogs Without Hydration Cost$escape$,
  $escape$Qwik's resumability means global UI state — toasts, modals, dialogs — must be serializable from day one. The right pattern is a `createContextId` store provided at the root layout via `useContextProvider`, consumed anywhere with `useContext`.

For a toast system, create a `ToastCtx` holding `{ items: ToastItem[] }`. In `root.tsx`, initialize with `useStore` and call `useContextProvider`. Any leaf component calls `useContext(ToastCtx)` and mutates directly. Wrap mutations in `$()` to keep them lazy-loadable QRLs — Qwik won't eagerly download the handler until invoked.

Modal state follows the same pattern: a `ModalCtx` with `open: boolean` and `payload: unknown`. For confirmation dialogs, encapsulate into a `useConfirm` hook returning a `confirm$` QRL. Internally, it sets a pending `useSignal<Deferred>`, renders the dialog bound to that signal, and resolves on user action.

Critically, because Qwik serializes context stores into the HTML stream during SSR, this state survives resumption with zero re-execution. Your entire global overlay layer adds no hydration penalty — the store is already live the moment the user interacts.$escape$,
  $escape$// root.tsx — provide store at app root
export const ToastCtx = createContextId<{ items: Toast[] }>('app/toast');

export default component$(() => {
  const toasts = useStore<{ items: Toast[] }>({ items: [] });
  useContextProvider(ToastCtx, toasts);
  return <Slot />;
});

// hooks/use-toast.ts — consume anywhere in the tree
export const useToast = () => {
  const ctx = useContext(ToastCtx);
  return {
    add: $((msg: string, type: 'info' | 'error' = 'info') =>
      ctx.items.push({ id: Date.now(), msg, type })),
    dismiss: $((id: number) => {
      ctx.items = ctx.items.filter(t => t.id !== id);
    }),
  };
};$escape$,
  $escape$typescript$escape$,
